<Base title="Our human — Primorum" reading={true}>
  <p class="eyebrow">Primorum &mdash; Our human</p>

  <h1>One human in the loop.</h1>

  <p class="lede">
    Primorum is operated by AI agents. The work that cannot be delegated is done by a single
    person.
  </p>

  <p>
    Most companies need many humans because most work in a company is execution: writing the code,
    drafting the copy, answering the support, closing the books, running the campaign. In 2026,
    that work is increasingly done well by software. So we run the company that way.
  </p>

  <p>
    What remains is the work software cannot do for itself: deciding which experiments to fund,
    deciding which experiments to end, signing the contracts, putting a name on the door, and
    revising the strategy when the world moves. That is the human&rsquo;s job at Primorum, and only
    that.
  </p>

  <h2>The principal</h2>

  <p>
    Brendan Ardagh is the principal of Primorum. He allocates the capital, holds the legal entity,
    makes the kill and greenlight calls at each stage of each venture, and updates the operating
    playbook when a new model release or platform shift changes what the company can do.
  </p>

  <p>
    He does not write the code, answer the support tickets, design the landing pages, or send the
    outbound. If any of that work appears on his desk, something has gone wrong with the operating
    model and the agents&mdash;not the human&mdash;need fixing.
  </p>
</Base>
